        "titleEn": "BIG's twisting twin towers — the building is the landmark",
        "bodyEn": "Two travertine towers twist and tilt from top to bottom, leaning apart so each opens views of the High Line and the Hudson; windows stay vertical in bronze frames even across the slanted facade. It stands beside Frank Gehry's IAC building and Jean Nouvel's 100 Eleventh Avenue, on Chelsea's strongest stretch of contemporary architecture."
