      "en": "Central Park Tower at 217 West 57th Street on Billionaires' Row is a supertall condominium by Extell Development, designed by Adrian Smith + Gordon Gill Architecture. At 1,550 feet (472 m) it is the tallest primarily residential building in the world. Just 179 residences, averaging roughly 5,000 sq ft, sit above a brand-new Nordstrom flagship, with interiors by Rottet Studio — a landmark that pairs unobstructed Central Park views with a marquee retail base."
